Dating: TUTHMOSIS III/MENKHEPERRE (not before); 18TH DYNASTY; AMENHOTEP III/AMENOPHIS III/NEBMAATRE (not after)
Name: Stela of Ded-ankhu
Description: The lunette contains two udjat-eyes flanking a shen-ring. Below this are two registers. In the upper register, a couple is sitting on a chair on the left, underneath, which is a kneeling girl. Facing them are a man with an incense burner and a woman. To the right is a man sitting on a stool, below which there is again a kneeling girl. A woman is standing next to him.In the lower register, the couple is again shown on a chair, below which the kneeling girl can be seen. Facing them are four people: a woman burning incense, a man, a woman and another man. There are inscriptions above the heads of the figures.
